  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "App Clip"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is a lightweight version of your app that offers users some of its functionality when and where they need it. Consider a coffee-shop app that users download from the App Store: It allows them to order a drink on their device, save favorite drinks, collect rewards, get special offers, and so on."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In contrast, the App Clip only offers the functionality to order a drink. When a user walks past the coffee shop, the system displays a location-based suggestion from Siri Suggestions on their device. They tap the suggestion, confirm the launch of the App Clip on the system-provided "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "App Clip card"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and instantly use the App Clip to order a drink."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3639578",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3639578",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Users find an App Clip by performing an "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "invocation"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "; for example, by tapping a location-based suggestion from Siri Suggestions or by scanning an NFC tag. The App Clip launches instantly, helps the user perform an everyday task as quickly as possible, and only stays on their device for as long as they need it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When a user installs an App Clip’s corresponding app, the full app replaces the App Clip. From this moment on, every invocation launches the full app instead of the App Clip, and the user gets the functionality of the App Clip within the full app. If they don’t install the full app, the system automatically removes the App Clip after a period of inactivity."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Again, consider the coffee shop’s App Clip: After use, the App Clip recommends its corresponding app to the user and they download the app. The next time they see the location-based suggestion and tap it, they launch the full app instead of the App Clip. If they don’t install the app, tapping the suggestion continues launching the App Clip."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Offer a Great User Experience",
          "anchor": "3599699"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "App Clips provide a polished user experience that helps users solve a real-world task as quickly as possible. Additionally, App Clips don’t appear on the Home screen, and users don’t manage them the way they manage full apps. Instead, the system removes an App Clip from a device after a period of inactivity, making a polished user experience even more important."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For design guidance, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Human Interface Guidelines",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/app-clips/overview/"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Review App Clip Creation",
          "anchor": "3671984"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "App Clips come with limitations to ensure a fast launch experience, protect user privacy, and preserve resources. Before you create an App Clip, first review technology that’s available to App Clips and identify which of your app’s functionality would make a great App Clip. When you’ve identified functionality that makes a great App Clip, creating an App Clip requires the following tasks:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Making changes to your app’s Xcode project and your code, for example, add an App Clip target, share code between App Clip and full app, and so on."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Making changes to your server to enable the system to verify your App Clip."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Creating your App Clip’s launch experience in App Store Connect and responding to invocations in your App Clip’s and your full app’s code."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
